#compdef any-sync-bundle
# ============================================================================
# _any-sync-bundle — zsh completion for **any-sync-bundle** —
#            grishy/any-sync-bundle, the **Anytype Self-Hosting
#            All-in-One bundle** — a single-binary launcher that
#            spins up the entire **Anytype** local-first knowledge-
#            management platform's server-side stack (coordinator
#            node + consensus node + filenode + sync node + the
#            embedded MongoDB + Redis dependencies) on the operator's
#            own infrastructure.  Anytype is the **end-to-end-
#            encrypted local-first knowledge-management application**
#            (Notion + Obsidian + Roam + Logseq alternative, 100k+
#            users) that is structurally designed around the
#            **any-sync** typed peer-to-peer sync protocol, with the
#            client running on every user device (iOS / Android /
#            macOS / Linux / Windows) and the typed sync server mesh
#            handling typed end-to-end-encrypted CRDT replication +
#            file storage across the user's devices.  Anytype Inc.
#            (Berlin) operates a default production sync mesh for
#            free-tier users, but the project deliberately publishes
#            the open-source `any-sync-*` server components under
#            MIT so operators can self-host the full backend — and
#            `any-sync-bundle` is **the** community-built operator
#            launcher that bundles all four typed any-sync server
#            components + the typed MongoDB + Redis dependencies +
#            the typed certificate-rotation lifecycle into one
#            single Go binary with a single config file.  Go=184
#            leader bump continuing Axis 129 (pure-Rust + pure-Go
#            peer-to-peer networking taxonomy) at 2/0/0 via the
#            canonical Go-side library **github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p**
#            (transitively required by the typed
#            github.com/anyproto/any-sync stack).
