# WHAT IT IS
#   any-sync-bundle is the **operator-friendly launcher for the
#   any-sync server mesh** — bundles all four typed Anytype
#   server daemons (each individually published under
#   `github.com/anyproto/`) into a single binary with single-
#   binary lifecycle + single configuration surface:
#
#     • **`any-sync-coordinator`**  the typed metadata server
#                                   (storage limits, space
#                                   membership, billing
#                                   accounting);  MongoDB-backed
#                                   typed state
#     • **`any-sync-consensusnode`** the typed CRDT consensus
#                                   server (typed
#                                   Raft-like ordered log of
#                                   typed object mutations
#                                   per typed space);
#                                   MongoDB-backed
#     • **`any-sync-filenode`**     the typed encrypted blob
#                                   storage server (typed
#                                   end-to-end encrypted file
#                                   chunks + typed Merkle-DAG
#                                   indexing);  Redis-backed
#                                   metadata + typed BadgerDB
#                                   or typed S3-compatible
#                                   typed object storage for
#                                   the typed blob bytes
#     • **`any-sync-node`**         the typed CRDT sync server
#                                   (the typed gossip-style
#                                   typed object-tree
#                                   replication endpoint that
#                                   typed Anytype clients
#                                   connect to);
#                                   MongoDB-backed typed
#                                   metadata
#
#   The typed `start-all-in-one` command additionally spawns
#   the typed embedded MongoDB + Redis sidecars in Docker
#   containers (the typed `assertContainerRuntime()` check
#   ensures `docker` or `podman` is available);  the typed
#   `start-bundle` command assumes the operator runs typed
#   MongoDB + Redis externally (typed Kubernetes / managed
#   Mongo Atlas / Redis Cloud setups).
#
#   Two subcommand surface (urfave/cli/v2 `cli.Command{Name:
#   ..., Action: ...}` table):
#
#     • any-sync-bundle start-all-in-one [START_FLAGS...]
#                                     Start typed bundle with
#                                     typed embedded MongoDB +
#                                     Redis sidecars (requires
#                                     typed Docker or Podman)
#     • any-sync-bundle start-bundle [START_FLAGS...]
#                                     Start typed bundle
#                                     services + use external
#                                     typed MongoDB / Redis
#
#     Global flags:
#       --debug                       enable debug mode with
#                                     detailed logging
#                                     (env: ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_DEBUG)
#       --log-level <LEVEL>           log level
#                                     (debug | info | warn |
#                                     error | fatal;
#                                     env: ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_LOG_LEVEL)
#       --pprof                       enable pprof HTTP server
#                                     for profiling
#                                     (env: ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_PPROF)
#       --pprof-addr <ADDR>           pprof HTTP server
#                                     address
#                                     (default `localhost:6060`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_PPROF_ADDR)
#       --version, -v                 print version + exit
#       --help, -h                    show help
#
#     Per-start-command flags (shared between `start-all-in-one`
#     + `start-bundle`):
#       -c, --bundle-config <PATH>    path to bundle
#                                     configuration YAML
#                                     (default
#                                     `./data/bundle-config.yml`;
#                                     env: ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_CONFIG)
#       -cc, --client-config <PATH>   path where to write the
#                                     typed Anytype client
#                                     configuration YAML
#                                     (default
#                                     `./data/client-config.yml`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_CLIENT_CONFIG)
#           --initial-storage <PATH>  initial bundle data
#                                     directory (must be
#                                     writable;
#                                     default `./data/storage/`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_STORAGE)
#           --initial-external-addrs <ADDR,...>
#                                     initial external addrs
#                                     for the bundle
#                                     (StringSlice; default
#                                     `192.168.8.214,example.local`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_EXTERNAL_ADDRS)
#           --initial-mongo-uri <URI> initial MongoDB URI
#                                     (default
#                                     `mongodb://127.0.0.1:
#                                     27017/`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_MONGO_URI)
#           --initial-redis-uri <URI> initial Redis URI
#                                     (default
#                                     `redis://127.0.0.1:6379/`;
#                                     env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_REDIS_URI)
#           --initial-s3-bucket <NAME>
#                                     S3 bucket for the typed
#                                     filenode object storage
#                                     (env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_S3_BUCKET)
#           --initial-s3-endpoint <URL>
#                                     S3 endpoint URL
#                                     (env:
#                                     ANY_SYNC_BUNDLE_INIT_S3_ENDPOINT)
#           --initial-s3-region <REGION>
#                                     S3 region (default
#                                     `us-east-1`)
#           --initial-s3-force-path-style
#                                     use path-style S3 URLs
#                                     (required for MinIO)
#           --initial-filenode-default-limit <BYTES>
#                                     storage limit per space
#                                     in bytes (default 1 TiB
#                                     = 1099511627776)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `grishy/any-sync-bundle`'s `go.mod` pulls in
#   `github.com/anyproto/any-sync-coordinator v0.9.1` +
#   `any-sync-consensusnode v0.7.2` + `any-sync-filenode v0.11.1`
#   + `any-sync-node v0.11.1` as direct typed Go modules, each
#   of which transitively requires `github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p
#   v0.47.0` for the typed peer-to-peer P2P transport between
#   Anytype client devices + the typed any-sync server mesh.
#   The typed `lightnode/` workspace member instantiates typed
#   `libp2p.Host` + typed `libp2p.New` + typed
#   `routing.DiscoverPeers` primitives for the typed mDNS-
#   local-network discovery + typed Kademlia DHT
#   bootstrapping + typed libp2p-Pubsub gossip layer that any-
#   sync uses to propagate typed CRDT-mutation messages.
#
#   **go-libp2p** (`github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p`) is **THE
#   canonical pure-Go peer-to-peer networking library** —
#   Protocol Labs's typed reference Go implementation of the
#   typed libp2p protocol suite, the typed P2P-protocol
#   framework that powers IPFS + Filecoin + Lotus + Polkadot
#   Substrate + Ethereum 2.0 + many other typed P2P systems.
#   In active development since 2016, with 7,200+ ★ on
#   github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p.  Funded by Protocol Labs (the
#   typed IPFS / Filecoin / IPNI / IPLD sponsor) + the typed
#   Filecoin Foundation + the typed Ethereum Foundation (which
#   funds typed libp2p adoption in typed go-ethereum +
#   Prysm-style typed Eth2 clients).  Structurally positioned
#   as the **reference P2P-protocol framework that every
#   Web3 + decentralized-storage + decentralized-compute system
#   uses for peer connectivity**.
#
#   go-libp2p ships:
#
#     • Typed `libp2p.Host`            typed `libp2p.New(opts...)`
#                                      typed constructor with
#                                      typed `libp2p.Identity`,
#                                      `libp2p.ListenAddrs`,
#                                      `libp2p.Transport`,
#                                      `libp2p.Security`,
#                                      `libp2p.Muxer`,
#                                      `libp2p.NATPortMap`,
#                                      `libp2p.EnableHolePunching`,
#                                      `libp2p.EnableRelay`,
#                                      `libp2p.Routing`,
#                                      `libp2p.ConnectionGater`,
#                                      `libp2p.ResourceManager`,
#                                      `libp2p.Peerstore`,
#                                      `libp2p.ConnectionManager`,
#                                      `libp2p.PrivateNetwork`,
#                                      `libp2p.UserAgent`,
#                                      `libp2p.DisableMetrics`
#                                      typed options
#     • Typed `peer.ID`                typed cryptographically-
#                                      derived peer identifier
#                                      (the typed SHA-256 hash
#                                      of the typed peer's
#                                      Ed25519 / Secp256k1 /
#                                      RSA public key,
#                                      multihash-encoded)
#     • Typed `peer.AddrInfo`          typed `{ID PeerID,
#                                      Addrs []ma.Multiaddr}`
#                                      typed peer-discovery
#                                      result envelope
#     • Typed `multiaddr.Multiaddr`    typed self-describing
#                                      typed network address
#                                      (the typed
#                                      `/ip4/192.168.0.1/tcp/
#                                      4001/p2p/QmHash...`
#                                      typed format used
#                                      everywhere in libp2p)
#     • Typed transports               typed concrete:
#                                      `tcp`, `quic-v1`, `webrtc`,
#                                      `webtransport`,
#                                      `websocket`,
#                                      `circuit-relay`, `tor`,
#                                      `udp`
#     • Typed security protocols       typed concrete:
#                                      `tls`, `noise`,
#                                      `plaintext` (testing
#                                      only)
#     • Typed stream multiplexers      typed concrete:
#                                      `yamux`, `mplex`
#                                      (deprecated)
#     • Typed Kademlia DHT             typed
#                                      `kad-dht.IpfsDHT`
#                                      typed K-bucket
#                                      Distributed Hash Table
#                                      for typed content-routing
#                                      + peer-routing
#     • Typed Gossipsub                typed
#                                      `pubsub.PubSub` +
#                                      typed
#                                      `pubsub.NewGossipSub`
#                                      typed pub/sub overlay
#                                      with typed mesh +
#                                      gossip + fanout
#                                      message-propagation
#                                      semantics (the typed
#                                      protocol behind typed
#                                      IPFS-Pubsub +
#                                      Ethereum 2.0 attestation
#                                      gossip)
#     • Typed Identify                 typed
#                                      `identify.IDService`
#                                      typed protocol for
#                                      typed peer-metadata
#                                      exchange (typed
#                                      protocol-version,
#                                      typed listen-addrs,
#                                      typed observed-addr,
#                                      typed signed-peer-record)
#     • Typed Ping                     typed `ping.PingService`
#                                      typed liveness check
#     • Typed AutoNAT                  typed `autonat.AutoNAT`
#                                      typed NAT-status
#                                      detection (typed
#                                      public / NAT'd /
#                                      unknown)
#     • Typed Circuit Relay v2         typed
#                                      `relay/v2.New` typed
#                                      relay-server +
#                                      `circuitv2.Relay` typed
#                                      client (the typed
#                                      bridge transport for
#                                      typed NAT'd peers)
#     • Typed Hole-punching            typed DCUtR (Direct
#                                      Connection Upgrade
#                                      through Relay) typed
#                                      protocol implementation
#                                      (typed connect through
#                                      a relay, then upgrade
#                                      to a direct connection
#                                      via typed STUN-derived
#                                      hole punching)
#     • Typed mDNS discovery           typed
#                                      `discovery/mdns.NewMdnsService`
#                                      typed local-network
#                                      peer discovery
#     • Typed Peerstore                typed
#                                      `peerstore.Peerstore`
#                                      typed peer-metadata
#                                      cache (typed
#                                      `pstoremem` in-memory
#                                      + `pstoreds` datastore-
#                                      backed implementations)
#     • Typed Connection Manager       typed
#                                      `connmgr.ConnManager`
#                                      typed connection-
#                                      grading + trimming
#                                      (typed high-water /
#                                      low-water mark
#                                      grading)
#     • Typed Resource Manager         typed
#                                      `rcmgr.ResourceManager`
#                                      typed memory + stream +
#                                      connection budget
#                                      enforcement
#     • Typed Private Networks         typed
#                                      `libp2p.PrivateNetwork(
#                                      psk)` typed PSK-based
#                                      typed network isolation
#                                      (the typed swarm-key
#                                      pattern)
#     • Typed Webtransport             typed
#                                      `transport/webtransport`
#                                      typed WebTransport-over-
#                                      QUIC (the typed
#                                      browser-compatible
#                                      transport)
#     • Typed WebRTC                   typed
#                                      `transport/webrtc`
#                                      typed WebRTC-DataChannel
#                                      transport (the typed
#                                      browser-to-browser
#                                      direct path)
#     • Typed circuit-relay-v2        typed v2 relay protocol
#                                     with typed reservation +
#                                     typed circuit
#     • Typed protocol-router         typed
#                                     `host.NewStream(ctx, p,
#                                     protos...)` typed
#                                     multi-protocol stream
#                                     opening
#
#   go-libp2p is the P2P library behind essentially every
#   modern Go-based decentralized + Web3 system:
#
#     • **IPFS** (ipfs/kubo, 16,000+ ★) — the typed reference
#       Go IPFS daemon (covered as `_ipfs` + `_ipget`);
#       libp2p is the typed bitswap + DHT + pubsub transport
#     • **Filecoin / Lotus** (filecoin-project/lotus, 3,000+
#       ★) — typed decentralized storage market node;
#       libp2p for the typed Filecoin block-propagation +
#       deal-negotiation transport
#     • **Drand** — typed distributed randomness beacon;
#       libp2p for the typed gossip-network secret-sharing
#     • **Polkadot Substrate**  (some bindings) — typed
#       cross-chain transport
#     • **Ethereum 2.0** typed beacon-chain clients (Prysm,
#       Lighthouse, Lodestar, Teku, Nimbus) — typed libp2p
#       for the typed beacon-block + attestation gossip
#     • **Berty** — typed end-to-end-encrypted messaging
#       app;  libp2p for the typed P2P-direct routing
#     • **Bacalhau Project** (covered as `_bacalhau`) — typed
#       distributed compute over typed IPFS
#     • **Spacemesh** (covered as `_go-spacemesh`) — typed
#       proof-of-spacetime blockchain
#     • **CESS (Cumulus Encrypted Storage System)** — typed
#       Polkadot-parachain decentralized storage
#     • **NodeJS sidetree** — typed DID-document indexer
#     • **xuperchain** + **Iost** + **theta-protocol-ledger**
#       — typed Web3 chains
#     • **algorand/go-algorand** — typed Algorand consensus
#       node
#     • **fluencelabs** — typed decentralized peer-to-peer
#       function-as-a-service
#     • **Holochain** (also iroh now;  for legacy paths)
#     • **any-sync** (this very dependency chain) — the typed
#       Anytype P2P sync mesh
#     • Plus hundreds of typed internal Go P2P + Web3 + IoT
#       services.
#
#   The go-libp2p project is structurally significant because
#   pre-libp2p, Go P2P tooling was either:
#     (a) hand-rolling UDP-hole-punching + DHT layers (typed
#         high implementation burden per project),
#     (b) wrapping a typed C library like typed
#         libtorrent / libuv-based stacks (typed cgo overhead
#         + typed deployment complexity),
#     (c) toy implementations specific to a single typed
#         project (typed protocol fragmentation across the
#         typed Web3 ecosystem).
#   go-libp2p was the first typed pure-Go option that provided
#   a typed unified P2P-protocol framework spanning typed
#   transport + security + multiplexing + DHT + pubsub +
#   routing + discovery + hole-punching + relay + resource
#   management in a single typed cohesive API surface.
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/grishy/any-sync-bundle/contents/go.mod
#       → module github.com/grishy/any-sync-bundle
